The codebase behaves like an early-stage architectural proof-of-concept. It requires stabilization across its asynchronous boundary points, robust serialization schemas, and strict process boundary sandboxing before it can be trusted safely in a production workspace environment.
Recommended Remediation Checklist
Add Async Controls: Implement CancellationToken tracking through AgentLoop.cs down to every unique worker instance.
Sanitize String Inputs: Enforce explicit character sanitization and regex limits on paths inside ToolArgumentNormalizer.cs.
Optimize Routing: Cache reflection lookups in ToolRouter.cs inside a thread-safe static directory dictionary during application startup.
Implement Buffered Stream Readers: Use an explicit string line buffer inside the TypeScript proxy to accumulate fragments until a full \n boundary is guaranteed.
Refactor Logging: Upgrade WorkerDispatcher.cs with an explicit application logging provider (ILogger) to ensure error states are transparently exposed.




